  <title>Sliding-Joint</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword>Definition<keyword>Prismatic Joint</keyword><keyword>Slide Joint</keyword></keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><table styleclass="PopupTable" rowcount="2" colcount="2">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:131px;">
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><image src="MD-Slide-Joint-Free.png" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"></image></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">A <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Slide-Joint</text> constrains <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Sketch-Element-Line" styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Lines</link>* from two separate <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">parts</text> to be collinear. (*<text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Lines</text> or <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">CAD-Lines</text>). </para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">The <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Symbols">symbol</link> for the <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Slide-Joint</text> is </para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><image src="Red-14-1b.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"></image>a narrow rectangle</para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><image src="Red-14-2.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"></image> a wide rectangle </para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><image src="Red-14-3.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"></image><text styleclass="Image Caption">&#32;</text>an arrowhead indicates the positive direction.</para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">Each rectangle is along the full length of each Line that you select to add the Slide-Joint.</para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#ff6600;" /></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td colspan="2">
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">A <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Slide-Joint</text> is also known as a <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Prismatic Joint</text>, or a <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Prismatic Pair</text>.</para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#ff6600;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="SeeAlso-small">See: <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Pin-Joint">Pin-Joint</link>, <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Ball-Joints">Ball-Joint</link></para>
          <para styleclass="SeeAlso-small">See also <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-FB-Motion-Dimension" anchor="SliderMotionDirection">Positive Direction of Sliders</link></para>
          <para styleclass="SeeAlso-small">See also <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Mechanism-Slide-Joint">Add Slide-Joint</link>, <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Mechanism-Pin-Joint">Add Pin-Joint</link>. <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Mechanism-Ball-Joint">Add Ball-Joint</link>. </para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
  </body>
</topic>
